      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2). This example features the 3.6L M96 flat-six, notably updated with a dual-row ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a new rear main seal. Power is delivered through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle paired with a recently installed Sachs clutch and a lightweight flywheel for improved throttle response. The chassis is dialed in with the M030 factory sport suspension package and staggered 18-inch Carrera II wheels wrapped in Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber. Braking performance remains sharp via four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers and vented rotors. This is a high-revving driver\u2019s car with a clean DME report and consistent oil analysis records. Ready for immediate spirited use.",
